59
00:02:31,110 --> 00:02:33,260
And the latest battle was fought in the new
trade deal

60
00:02:33,260 --> 00:02:35,550
between the US, Mexico and Canada.

61
00:02:35,550 --> 00:02:39,060
The United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement,

62
00:02:39,060 --> 00:02:41,599
USMCA, which will replace NAFTA,

63
00:02:41,599 --> 00:02:45,769
has some clauses built into it that will affect
China trade.

64
00:02:45,769 --> 00:02:47,099
Take article 32.10.

65
00:02:47,099 --> 00:02:49,590
It’s about free trade negotiations

66
00:02:49,590 --> 00:02:51,950
with non market economies.

67
00:02:51,950 --> 00:02:54,300
China is considered a non market economy.

68
00:02:54,300 --> 00:02:56,290
The clause gives all three countries the power

69
00:02:56,290 --> 00:02:59,150
to block each other from making free-trade

70
00:02:59,150 --> 00:03:01,620
agreements with China without approval.

71
00:03:01,620 --> 00:03:04,379
It effectively gives the US more power in

72
00:03:04,379 --> 00:03:08,950
“weakening Beijing’s negotiating power
in future trade talks”.

73
00:03:08,950 --> 00:03:11,950
